sentences: Brady Seals (born March 29, 1969) is an American country music artist.
He is the cousin of Jim Seals (of Seals & Crofts) and Dan Seals, Johnny Duncan, the nephew of Troy Seals, and father of Evan Seals, who was born September 15, 2008.
Seals made his debut in 1988 as co-lead vocalist and keyboardist in the sextet Little Texas, with whom he recorded until his departure in late 1994.
Seals made his debut in 1988 as co-lead vocalist and keyboardist in the sextet Little Texas, with whom he recorded until his departure in late 1994.
Between then and 2002, he recorded as a solo singer, releasing three studio albums and charting in the Top 40 on the country charts with "Another You, Another Me".
In 2002, Seals formed a quartet called Hot Apple Pie, in which he has recorded one studio album and charted three singles.
A fourth solo album, Play Time, was released in 2009 via Star City.
Seals spent six years with Little Texas, playing keyboards and co-writing all of the band's major hits.
By late 1994, shortly after the release of their third album, Kick a Little, Seals had left the group and began a solo career.
He signed to Reprise Records and released his debut album, The Truth, in 1996.
Another album, the self-titled Brady Seals, was issued in 1998 via Reprise Records' parent label, Warner Bros. Records, 2003's Thompson Street, released via Image Entertainment
